OL,3,CParents working from home 'makes
OL,4,Cchildren feel school is optional' -
OL,5,COfsted head
OL,7,FAttendance rates are suffering because
OL,8,Fchildren whose parents work from home
OL,9,Ffeel going to school is optional, the
OL,10,Fhead of Ofsted has reportedly claimed.
OL,12,FSir Martyn Oliver, chief inspector at
OL,13,Fthe education watchdog, said the
OL,14,Fculture of not going into the office
OL,15,Fevery day had broken the daily habit
OL,16,Fof "putting your shoes on instead of
OL,17,Fyour slippers" and going out to work.
