OL,3,CParents working from home 'makes
OL,4,Cchildren feel school is optional' -
OL,5,COfsted head
OL,7,FHe added: "I think developing good
OL,8,Fsocial habits of getting up in the
OL,9,Fmorning, putting your shoes on instead
OL,10,Fof your slippers, going to school,
OL,11,Fexpecting to complete a full day's
OL,12,Fschool, a full day's work ` clearly
OL,13,Fthat's habit forming.
OL,15,F"Nationally, Fridays have always been
OL,16,Fthe worst attendance day (for
OL,17,Fschools), but then I look at
OL,18,FWestminster (where Ofsted is based)
OL,19,Fand I see the place clearing out on a
OL,20,FThursday night very often. Again, is
OL,21,Fthere something in that?"
